Shared objects:

    .so     - linux (shared object)
    .dll    - windows (dynamic linked library)
    .dylib  - mac (dynamic library)


> gcc 

  -f flag
        PIC    Position Independent Code
               The job of the linker is relcation and resolution of symbols. -fPIC is needed to make shared libraries work.
  -shared
  -o        output


$ tree
.
├── include
│   ├── cmath.h
│   └── cmult.h
└── src
    ├── cmath.c
    ├── cmult.c
    └── main.c

2 directories, 5 files

Create the shared libraries:

    $ gcc -fPIC -shared ./src/cmath.c -I./include -o cmath.so
    $ ls
    cmath.so  include  src
    ~~~~~~~~

    $ gcc -fPIC -shared ./src/cmult.c -I./include -o cmult.so
    $ ls
    cmath.so  cmult.so  include  src
    ~~~~~~~~  ~~~~~~~~